      "depth": 1,
      "type_signature": "(signal: array-like numeric signal, sampling_rate: float) -> array-like numeric signal",
      "matched_primitive": null,
      "is_optional": false,
      "is_opaque": false,
      "is_external": false,
      "parallelizable": false,
      "conceptual_summary": "log-domain_multiplicative_component_filter. Maps a positive-valued 1-D sequence (or compatible tensor) into a logarithmic domain so multiplicative factors become additive components. Applies a frequency-selective linear filter parameterized by sampling frequency in that transformed domain, then maps back with an exponential inverse transform. The result suppresses slowly varying multiplicative envelopes while retaining faster structural variations on the same temporal support.. Applications: Preconditioning seismic or geophysical traces to separate multiplicative propagation effects from reflectivity-like fine structure., Normalizing biomedical waveform channels (e.g., electrophysiology or photometric streams) where multiplicative baseline drift obscures transient events., Enhancing rotating-machinery condition signals by removing slow multiplicative envelope variation before fault-pattern analysis., Flattening multiplicative gain trends in remote-sensing or spectroscopy time-series prior to anomaly detection.",
      "critic_notes": "",
      "decomposition_rationale": ""
    },
